  "texts": [
    "Artificially intelligent polling overcomes this limit.",
    "Remarkably, it is able to make representative inference for granular population categories by bringing in auxiliary information from multiple data sources, and cleverly aggregating these, via 'regression and post-stratification' algorithms.",
    "MrP (Gelman and Little 1997; Park et al. 2004), the most widely implemented amongst these, is able to do more with less: it can make accurate inference at granular levels of analysis from the same samples for which traditional methods fail.",
    "It is able to do so by leveraging correlations across areas and demographics, essentially assuming a degree of exchangeability between voter-types with similar demographic and socio-political profiles.",
    "The marriage between MrP and Big Data provides the power to increase granularity further, and enables predictions at the level of a postcode, precinct, village etc."
  ],
